{
  "texts": [
    "In fact, several potential issues in the small-scale structure of the Universe, such as the cusp vs core (Flores & Primack 1994; Moore 1994; Karukes et al. 2015) or the missing satellite (Klypin et al. 1999; Moore et al. 1999) problems, could be disposed of or, at least, mitigated assuming that dark matter is made of ultralight particles.",
    "As predicated by Khmelnitsky & Rubakov (2014), the presence of ULDM induces harmonic delays in the arrival times, with a frequency proportional to the ultralight boson mass.",
    "In this paper, we provide a broad overview of the implications of the signal observed in the second data release of the EPTA+InPTA (EPTA Collaboration 2023) for the different physical processes mentioned above.",
    "More in-depth analysis of several of these scenarios will be the subject of separate future publications.",
    "Unless otherwise stated, we consider each process separately, and we discuss the implications of the detected signal under the hypothesis that it is generated by that specific process."
  ]
}